Verb(Adverb)

Subject(Subject - Adjective/Prep Phrase)...

(Conjunction Subject Subject - Adjective/Prep Phrase)...

Object(Object - Adjective/Prep Phrase)...

(Conjunction Object Object - Adjective/Prep Phrase)...

[Punctuation: STOP/Elipses/Repeat of punctuation at start for emphasis]



Note: to use a Verb as a noun (a gerund): Subject/Object Gerund (Verb)

The "Ordinal Tag" can be associated with any noun: Pronoun Subject or Object by prepending it followed by a number (usually 1 2 3). Afterwards the Ordinal Tag and the number can replace the noun until the number is associated with another noun.

Singular is the default.
Pronouns are created by combining modifiers in the order presented. For "We" where it is a masculine person with other males and one female would be: "SelfMaleOtherFemalePluralMale".

Note that: "Self/You/Other/Possessive/Reflexive" are only included once. Person is Self/You/Other/Self+You/Self+Other. (Cannot have You and Other together). Gender is one of: Unknown Neuter Feminine Masculine. Unknown is the default gender but may need to be explicitely included if it is needed to combine with other genders.

Other is only required after Self by itself Other is the same as OtherPluralFemalePluralMale and OtherPlural means more than one but genders are uncertain. You cannot have a single unknown and any other single.
